docs.abstract: After his breakthrough win in NASCAR’s top series, only the second such victory by a Black driver at that level, Wallace talked about learning to shut out ugly noise and to focus on what matters most.
docs.snippet: After his breakthrough win in NASCAR’s top series, only the second such victory by a Black driver at that level, Wallace talked about learning to shut out ugly noise and to focus on what matters most.
docs.lead_paragraph: Bubba Wallace’s fiancée, Amanda Carter, supplied the positivity. Their Aussiedoodle, Asher, brought the joy. Denny Hamlin and Michael Jordan put Wallace in a fast car, and on Monday he joined Wendell Scott, becoming the second Black driver to win a race at NASCAR’s highest level.

headline.main: Bubba Wallace Is Ebullient, Defiant and Comfortable
headline.print_headline: ‘You Do This to Be the Best’: Wallace  Keeps Focus on Racing and It Pays Off

docs.abstract: Twenty-somethings rolling their eyes at the habits of their elders is a longstanding trend, but many employers said there’s a new boldness in the way Gen Z dictates taste.
docs.snippet: Twenty-somethings rolling their eyes at the habits of their elders is a longstanding trend, but many employers said there’s a new boldness in the way Gen Z dictates taste.
docs.lead_paragraph: As a millennial with a habit of lurking on TikTok, Jessica Fain understood that skinny jeans and side parts were on the steady march toward extinction. But when Ms. Fain, who works as a product manager at a large tech company, heard that some of her favorite emojis might also be confronting retirement — namely that laughing-sobbing face — she decided to seek the counsel of her junior colleagues.

headline.main: The 37-Year-Olds Are Afraid of the 23-Year-Olds Who Work for Them
headline.print_headline: The 23-Year-Olds Want to Run the Office
